article.headline: Coppin St 54, Norfolk State 39
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Nicholas King scored 15 points, Raheem Scott had 12 and Coppin State scored almost half its points off turnovers in a 54-39 victory against Norfolk State on Monday night. The Eagles (8-11, 8-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) used an 8-0 run late in the first half to open a 28-14 lead by halftime and never led by fewer than 13 again. Norfolk State (8-10, 6-4) turned the ball over 25 times, leading to 24 points for the visiting Eagles. The Spartans got 10 points each from Karandick Ogunride and Chakowby Hicks, but shot just 27.8 percent and made just 1 of 13 3-point attempts. Coppin State won despite shooting just 30.5 percent.
